        "id": "582c274cd318a914",
        "text": "The starting point of every learning process in German lessons is the careful perception of a section of the world, the scope of which can be narrower or wider in view of the respective situation. This begins with the planning of the lesson; the teacher must first go through this process alone, with its possible extensions already in mind. Then the teacher goes through the process together with the students. Perception is a dialogical relationship process that basically concerns all \"actors\" equally - all are entitled to attention. Perception means to get in touch with the world, to enter into a relationship with the subject matter, to allow resonances. However, this also means that the process of perception changes as soon as further actors (the students), their ideas, their previous knowledge and their attitudes are included in this process. Thus, teaching can only be planned up to a certain point.\n"
